<h1 class="title">Debugging</h1>
<p>
	The tools on this page can be used to debug sync issues with Joplin Server.
</p>

<div class="debug-tools-container">
	<fieldset class="resource-check-container" id="note-on-server-check">
		<legend>
			Check if an item (note, notebook, resource, tag) is present on the server
		</legend>
		<label for="note-on-server-input">External link or ID:</label>
		<input type="text" id="note-on-server-input"/>
		<noscript>JavaScript required</noscript>
	</fieldset>

	<fieldset class="resource-check-container" id="note-in-diff-check">
		<legend>
			Check if an item is sent to a Joplin client to download during an initial sync
		</legend>
		<label for="note-on-server-input">External link or ID:</label>
		<input type="text" id="note-in-diff-input"/>
		<noscript>JavaScript required</noscript>
	</fieldset>
</div>

<hr/>

<div class="usage-container">
	<h2 class="title is-2" id="getting-an-id">Getting an external link or ID</h2>
	<p>
		The above tools accept either an item ID, an internal link to an item, or an external link
		to an item. Here's how you can get these:
	</p>

	<details class="usage-section">
		<summary class="title">Getting an external notebook link on desktop</summary>

		<p>This is an example external notebook link: <code>joplin://x-callback-url/openFolder?id=54b111edd8664a5c8ece04d80ac7b9ae</code></p>

		<ol>
			<li>Right-click on a notebook (in the notebook list).</li>
			<li>In the right-click menu, click "copy external link"</li>
		</ol>
	</details>

	<details class="usage-section">
		<summary class="title">Getting an external note link on desktop</summary>

		<ol>
			<li>Right-click on a note (in the notes list).</li>
			<li>Click "copy external link"</li>
		</ol>
	</details>


	<details class="usage-section">
		<summary class="title">Getting an external note link on mobile</summary>

		<ol>
			<li>Open a note</li>
			<li>Open the actions menu (the three vertical dots on the top right of the screen).</li>
			<li>Click "Copy markdown link"</li>
		</ol>
	</details>

</div>